printf("Element at Y: %d\n", arr[Y]);

3. The sum (from your original exercise):

c

printf("Sum: %d\n", arr[X] + arr[Y]);

Key Concept

arr  alone = memory address (use with %p )

arr[index]  = actual value (use with %d )

